      <p>
        datapanick assumes that clarity is always purchased at a cost.
        The cost is usually invisible because it is paid upstream:
        in framing, in compression, in what never entered the system.
      </p>

      <p>
        The task is not to remove mediation, but to make its pressure legible.
      </p>

